# Extension alarms (background + OS notifications)

Tabocalypse alarms must work **without** an open new-tab page. The browser tracks scheduled times via **`browser.alarms`**; the **MV3 service worker** ([`background.ts`](../../apps/extension/entrypoints/background.ts)) is the only place that handles `onAlarm` and shows reminders.

## Architecture

| Layer | Responsibility |
|-------|----------------|
| **Clock HUD panel (`ClockAlarmsSection`)** | Form UI, validation of user input, list display |
| **`tabocalypse-alarm-client.ts`** | `runtime.sendMessage` for schedule/delete |
| **`tabocalypse-alarm-service.ts`** | `browser.alarms.create/clear`, `alarmMeta` storage, `handleTabocalypseAlarmFired` |
| **`tabocalypse-alarm-notification.ts`** | `browser.notifications.create` (OS notification — **default and only** delivery path) |

## Do

- Route **schedule** and **delete** through **`scheduleTabocalypseAlarmViaBackground`** / **`deleteTabocalypseAlarmViaBackground`** so the service worker owns alarm side effects.
- Fire reminders only from **`handleTabocalypseAlarmFired`** → **`showTabocalypseAlarmNotification`**.
- **`browser.alarms.onAlarm`** listener must **return** the async handler promise so the MV3 service worker stays alive until **`notifications.create`** finishes (Windows drops notifications if the worker exits early).
- Use **`ALARM_PREFIX`**, **`META_KEY`**, and **`isTabocalypseAlarm`** from [`alarm-meta.ts`](../../apps/extension/lib/alarm-meta.ts).
- Keep **`alarms`** and **`notifications`** in [`wxt.config.ts`](../../apps/extension/wxt.config.ts) manifest permissions.

## Do not

- Add **`browser.alarms.onAlarm`** listeners in the new-tab React app.
- Deliver alarm reminders with **in-tab HUD toasts** instead of **`browser.notifications`**.
- Call **`browser.alarms.create`** / **`clear`** directly from UI code — use the background client.

## User-facing copy

The **Clock** panel alarms section should state that reminders run in the **background** and the **new tab can be closed**; mention **system notifications** and browser/OS permission if delivery may fail.
